    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"ddb\">\n<p>You draw the moisture from every creature in a 30-foot &amp;Reference[cube]{cube} centered on a point you choose within range. Each creature in that area must make a &amp;Reference[con]{Constitution} saving throw. Constructs and &amp;Reference[undead]{undead} aren’t affected, and plants and water elementals make this saving throw with disadvantage. A creature takes 12d8 &amp;Reference[necrotic]{necrotic} damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">Nonmagical plants in the area that aren’t creatures, such as trees and shrubs, wither and die instantly.</p>\n</div>",
